{
  "texts": [
    "For example, the long jump consists of three sub-sequences: run-up, take-off, and landing.",
    "In full supervision, it is easy to learn the complete action from the comments.",
    "However, in weak supervision, due to the lack of time boundary annotation, the integrity modeling of the action needs additional research.",
    "The CMCS proposed by Liu et al. (2019a) in 2019 uses a multi-branch network and diversity loss to ensure dissimilarity between the class activation sequences output by different branches, thus training each branch to locate different parts of the action.",
    "Aggregating activations can retrieve the complete action from multiple branches."
  ]
}